    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ 400\u00b0F/ Gas 6</p> <p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong><strong>\u00a0oil</strong> over a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong>\u00a0<strong>shallot</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and finely dice the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> to the shallot, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p> <p>Increase the heat to high and cook for 4 min or until\u00a0browned and caramelised</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crumble\u00a0the<strong>\u00a0<span style=\"background-color:#ffff00;\">chestnut</span>\u00a0mushrooms</strong> into bite-sized pieces using your hands</p> <p>Dissolve the<strong> beef\u00a0stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong>\u00a0in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013\u00a0this is your<strong>\u00a0tomato stock</strong></p> <p>Grate the<strong>\u00a0cheddar cheese\u00a0</strong></p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, add the<strong>\u00a0diced carrot</strong>\u00a0to the pan and cook for 2 min</p> <p>Add the <strong>crumbled mushrooms</strong> and <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min\u00a0</p> <p>Add the<strong>\u00a0tomato stock </strong>and cook for 5 min or until thickened to a rag\u00f9-like consistency</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p> <p>Once melted, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong>\u00a0&amp; stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p> <p>Add 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [700ml]</span><strong> milk</strong>\u00a0gradually &amp; whisk for 5-8 min or until a smooth, thick sauce\u00a0remains</p> <p>Remove from the heat, season with <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0&amp;\u00a0<strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0and stir through the <strong>cheese</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Layer some<span class=\"text-danger\">\u00a0</span>of the <strong>rag\u00f9</strong>\u00a0over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with 3 <strong>lasagne sheets</strong></p> <p>Repeat this process until you end up with\u00a0a final layer of <strong>lasagne sheets\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Tip: you may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish!</p> <p>Top with the <strong>b\u00e9chamel</strong>, ensuring all of the pasta is covered and cook in the oven for 30-35 min or until the pasta is cooked</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-lasagne-red-gem-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p> <p>Wash, then chop the <strong>red\u00a0gem</strong> in half, lengthways</p> <p>Serve the cooked <strong>lasagne</strong> with the <strong>red gem</strong> on the side, drizzle with the\u00a0<strong>dressing</strong> and enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
